# Playwright E2E tests

Config: `playwright.config.ts`. Scenario plans: `specs/` (notably `specs/funkysi1701-test-plan.md`). CI map: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).

## Running tests

```bash
npm ci
npx playwright install chromium   # if needed
npm test                          # full suite
npm run test:smoke                # @smoke subset (homepage, 404, sitemap)
```

- **`BASE_URL`:** `playwright.config.ts` defaults to `https://www.funkysi1701.com` when unset. Use `http://localhost:1313` for `hugo server -D`, or another preview URL.
- After changing `package.json` or `package-lock.json`, run `npm ci` before `npm test`.
- Mark lightweight PR scenarios with Playwright tag `{ tag: '@smoke' }` so `npm run test:smoke` / `playwright-smoke.yml` pick them up.

## CI expectations

- **PR smoke (issue #3275):** **`playwright-smoke.yml`** runs on all pull requests against a local Hugo production server (`BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:1313`, `--grep @smoke`, job timeout 10 minutes). This tests PR changes; it is not a substitute for the full suite.
- **Full E2E gate:** **`swa-deploy-nonprod.yml`** deploys to blog-dev then runs Playwright on pushes to **`develop`** and **`feature/*`** (`BASE_URL=https://blog-dev.funkysi1701.com`). **`playwright.yml`** runs on pushes to **`main`** and PRs into **`main`**: PRs use blog-dev (feature not on production yet); pushes / `workflow_dispatch` use production.
- Full suite runs `scripts/generate-page-coverage.js`; Codecov upload when `CODECOV_TOKEN` is set. `codecov.yml` treats page coverage as **informational**.

## Spec traceability

- Start test files with a `// spec: specs/...` comment pointing at the scenario doc (e.g. `// spec: specs/funkysi1701-test-plan.md`).
- Run `npm run check:spec-headers` after adding specs; CI fails if any `tests/**/*.spec.ts` omits the header.
- Keep `specs/` and tests aligned when behaviour changes.

## Hugo feedback

For template or content changes, `hugo server -D` or a production `hugo` build helps validate before or after E2E runs.
